# Critical Deployment Workflow (No Exceptions)

- Always follow this sequence for any code change:
  1) local edit and verify
  2) local git commit
  3) git push to remote
  4) server update only via `git pull`

- Never deploy via direct file copy (`scp`, `rsync`, manual edits on server) before commit/push.
- If production is broken, still create a local commit first, push immediately, then apply `git pull` on server.
- After every urgent fix, confirm local `git status` is clean and server commit equals remote HEAD.
- If this workflow cannot be completed, stop and report blocker instead of bypassing the process.
